cwe_description: A program attempts to read data from a buffer using an index that is too small.
explanation: The code lacks proper bounds checking when accessing `object->list.objects[1]->list.objects[0]`. If the ASN.1 structure is malformed and `object->list.objects[1]` does not have a list of length 1, accessing `object->list.objects[1]->list.objects[0]` will result in a segmentation fault or other memory corruption.
